SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 81
BY SENATOR STINE AND REPRESENTATIVE GEYMANN
COMMENDATIONS. Commends and congratulates the Westlake High School Rams
baseball team upon winning the 2026 Louisiana High School Athletic Association Non-
Select Division III Baseball Championship.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend and congratulate the Westlake High School Rams baseball team upon winning
3 the 2026 Louisiana High School Athletic Association Non-Select Division III
4 Baseball Championship and to recognize the team for its outstanding perseverance,
5 sportsmanship, and historic achievement.
6 WHEREAS, the Westlake High School Rams baseball program has established itself
7 as one of the premier athletic programs in southwest Louisiana through years of dedication,
8 discipline, and teamwork; and
9 WHEREAS, the Rams have enjoyed one of the most successful stretches in program
10 history over the past several seasons, advancing to the quarter finals in 2024, the semifinals
11 in 2025, and now capturing the program's first state championship in thirty years; and
12 WHEREAS, the second-seeded Rams completed an impressive post season run by
13 defeating nationally respected opponents and earning a dramatic semifinal series victory
14 over Doyle High School before advancing to the championship series; and
15 WHEREAS, the Rams demonstrated extraordinary determination and resilience in
16 overcoming defending powerhouse Sterlington in a best-of-three championship series and
17 secured the Louisiana High School Athletic Association Non-Select Division III Baseball
18 Championship with a decisive 7-2 victory in game three; and
