1 WHEREAS, junior pitcher Mason Conrad delivered a remarkable championship
2 performance, throwing a complete game while allowing only three hits against one of the
3 state's most prolific offenses and earning Most Outstanding Player honors for the
4 championship series; and
5 WHEREAS, the leadership of Head Coach Blake Reed, Assistant Coaches Ethan
6 Logan, Keith Lemelle, Caleb Abshire, and Rieland Devillier, together with the contributions
7 of student manager, Ethan Soileau and student-athlete seniors, Brody Boudreaux, Kyce
8 Benoit, Cooper Cryer, Hadley Hardesty, Peyton Kile, Graydon Ross, Sawyer Vidrine, and
9 Cooper Williams; juniors, Brody Anderson, Brayden Boyer, Mason Conrad, Dax Duhon,
10 and Jett Quebodeaux; sophomores, Kole Duhon, Greyson Johnson, and Landen Soileau; and
11 freshmen, Hunter Babineaux, Joseph Benavides, Denver Bird, Evan Boudreaux, Cooper
12 Bordelon, Tyler Buller, Landon Dixon, Carson Harrington, Isaac Jordan, Julian Lester,
13 Kayden Marshall, Jayden Mitchell, Rylee Nelson, and Tyler Ross exemplified the values of
14 teamwork, sacrifice, discipline, and excellence that define Louisiana high school athletics;
15 and
16 WHEREAS, the Rams' relentless effort, strategic play, and unselfish commitment
17 to one another inspired their school, alumni, and the entire Westlake community; and
18 WHEREAS, the 2026 Westlake Rams baseball team has brought immense pride and
19 recognition to the city of Westlake, Calcasieu Parish, and the state of Louisiana through a
20 championship season that will long be remembered in the proud history of Louisiana high
21 school sports.
22 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
23 commend and congratulate the Westlake High School Rams baseball team upon winning the
24 2026 Louisiana High School Athletic Association Non-Select Division III Baseball
25 Championship and does hereby recognize the players, coaches, school officials, families, and
26 supporters whose dedication and spirit made this extraordinary achievement possible.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to Head
28 Baseball Coach Blake Reed.
